### Configuring Model Aliases

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/help/faq.md

Shows how to define custom aliases for AI models in the OpenClaw configuration. These aliases simplify model selection via slash commands.

```json5
{
  agents: {
    defaults: {
      model: { primary: "anthropic/claude-opus-4-5" },
      models: {
        "anthropic/claude-opus-4-5": { alias: "opus" },
        "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5": { alias: "sonnet" },
        "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5": { alias: "haiku" }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Model Allowlist with Aliases

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/concepts/models.md

Example JSON5 configuration demonstrating how to set a primary model and define aliases for other models within the agent configuration. This controls which models are available for use.

```json5
{
  agent: {
    model: { primary: "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5" },
    models: {
      "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5": { alias: "Sonnet" },
      "anthropic/claude-opus-4-5": { alias: "Opus" }
    }
  }
}
```

