### Local OpenAI-Compatible Proxy Configuration

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/gateway/local-models.md

This configuration enables OpenClaw to connect to any local LLM serving via an OpenAI-compatible API endpoint (e.g., vLLM, LiteLLM). It requires specifying the `baseUrl`, `apiKey`, and the model details. This setup allows flexibility in choosing different local model serving solutions.

```json5
{
  "models": {
    "mode": "merge",
    "providers": {
      "local": {
        "baseUrl": "http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1",
        "apiKey": "sk-local",
        "api": "openai-responses",
        "models": [
          {
            "id": "my-local-model",
            "name": "Local Model",
            "reasoning": false,
            "input": ["text"],
            "cost": { "input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0 },
            "contextWindow": 120000,
            "maxTokens": 8192
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

