### Configure MiniMax M2.1 as Fallback in OpenClaw

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/providers/minimax.md

This JSON configuration sets up MiniMax M2.1 as a fallback model in OpenClaw, with 'anthropic/claude-opus-4-5' as the primary model. This ensures that if the primary model is unavailable, requests will be routed to MiniMax M2.1. It defines aliases for both models.

```json5
{
  env: { MINIMAX_API_KEY: "sk-..." },
  agents: {
    defaults: {
      models: {
        "anthropic/claude-opus-4-5": { alias: "opus" },
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.1": { alias: "minimax" }
      },
      model: {
        primary: "anthropic/claude-opus-4-5",
        fallbacks: ["minimax/MiniMax-M2.1"]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

