### Analyze Images with Configured Model (OpenCLAW Image)

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/tools/index.md

Analyze an image using the configured image model. Requires an image path or URL and an optional prompt. The model can be overridden, and a size cap can be applied. This functionality is available when an image model is configured or can be inferred.

```json
{
  "image": "/path/to/your/image.jpg",
  "prompt": "Describe this image.",
  "model": "vision-model-name",
  "maxBytesMb": 10
}
```

